learn SICP
exercise 1.9 & 1.10
Sat Jul 11, 2026  10:30 PM CST

EXERCISE 1.9

  Program 1 (Recursive)                         Program 2 (Iterative)

  (define (+ a b)                               (define (+ a b)
    (if (= a 0)                                   (if (= a 0)
        b                                             b
        (inc (+ (dec a) b))))                         (+ (dec a) (inc b))))

  Evaluation of (+ 3 4):                        Evaluation of (+ 3 4):
  (+ 3 4)                                       (+ 3 4)
  (inc (+ 2 4))                                 (+ 2 5)
  (inc (inc (+ 1 4)))                           (+ 1 6)
  (inc (inc (inc (+ 0 4))))                     (+ 0 7)
  (inc (inc (inc 4)))                           7
  (inc (inc 5))
  (inc 6)
  7

Key point: Recursion vs iteration depends on deferred operations, not on whether
the procedure calls itself.

EXERCISE 1.10

Program:
  (define (A x y)
    (cond ((= y 0) 0)
          ((= x 0) (* 2 y))
          ((= y 1) 2)
          (else (A (- x 1)
                   (A x (- y 1))))))

Values:
  (A 1 10) = 1024
  (A 2 4)  = 65536
  (A 3 3)  = 65536

Definitions:
  (define (f n) (A 0 n))   →  f(n) = 2n
  (define (g n) (A 1 n))   →  g(n) = 2^n
  (define (h n) (A 2 n))   →  h(n) = 2 ↑↑ n  (power tower of n 2's)
  (define (k n) (* 5 n n)) →  k(n) = 5n²

