Chapter 2 of CSAPP is mainly about how computers store and process information
---essentially, it's all about memory. For the mini-project in this section, I
wanted to try implementing a fully functional calculator using only bitwise
operations, and also write something like a Python shell.

2.1.1 introduces hexadecimal notation. Since I'm already very familiar with it,
I went straight to the 'mathematical' exercises in this section.

